[Secuil Kilas Balik QL] "Kamu berani nggak ?" tanya beliau di malam itu, dengan kondisi diriku yang telanjur seseggukan dan dengan wajah tidak karuan. "Oke, saya ganti pertanyaannya, kamu mau nggak ?". Sepertinya beliau tidak bisa menunggu jawaban yang (lebih) jelas dan yakin dariku yang masih tidak karuan rupanya. Di akhir kala itu, beliau memancingku untuk kembali tersenyum, walaupun akhirnya malah beliau yang terbahak-bahak.

Namun ada satu momen yang berkesan untukku, yaitu ketika beliau memberi pertanyaan retoris, kira-kira bila dijadikan pesan akan seperti ini :

Sesungguhnya kenangan akan tetap ada walau tidak ada komunikasi. ---------------
Saat itu perjuangan batinku dimulai. 
Aku bertekad untuk melangkah pelan-pelan meninggalkan memori kelam itu, racun yang berselimutkan kebahagiaan semu. "You never walk alone" pungkasnya demikian.

Tribute to Ayrton Senna. Comemmorating 21st anniversary of his death (1 May 1994 - 1 May 2015).
Ayrton Senna da Silva was a legendary Brazilian racing driver. He won 3 F1 World Championships (1988, 1990, 1991) and won 41 races during his active years. 
He was killed on 1 May 1994 in an accident while leading the 1994 San Marino Grand Prix, which was held on the "Autodromo Enzo e Dino Ferrari" circuit, Imola, Italy.
Senna's grave bears the epitaph "Nada pode me separar do amor de Deus," which means "Nothing can separate me from the love of God" (Romans 8 : 38-39).
Although he was among the most dominant and successful F1 drivers of the modern era and is considered by many as the greatest racing driver of all time, he was humble and faithful, both to God and to his family. (Data source : Wikipedia)
